cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.PF 

This paper deals with scheduling coflows in datacenter networks, which involves communication patterns and network optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions datacenter networks, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as another likely category. The problem of minimizing completion time involves optimization and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). Finally, the paper mentions approximation algorithms, which could also fall under cs.PF (Probability and Statistics).
